# firstone Development Guidelines

Auto-generated from feature plans; **authoritative plan**: `specs/app-base/plan.md`. Last updated: 2026-03-29

## Active Technologies
- TypeScript (strict) — client and server; Node.js 20+ + React 19, Vite (SPA); `@auth0/auth0-spa-js` + Auth0 Universal Login (PKCE); **Fastify** HTTP API; **Drizzle ORM** + **`postgres`** driver; **Drizzle Kit** for migrations; `jose` or `jwks-rsa` for JWT validation (001-bootstrap-session-timer)
- **PostgreSQL 15+** (primary, server truth); optional `localStorage`/IndexedDB client cache for resilience (v1: online-first) (001-bootstrap-session-timer)
- TypeScript (strict); Node.js 20+ + **Next.js 14+** (App Router); **`@auth0/nextjs-auth0`** (Regular Web App session + callback); **Drizzle ORM** + **`postgres`** driver; **Drizzle Kit** for migrations; React 19 (001-exercise-app)
- **Neon PostgreSQL** (serverless, pooled) via `NETLIFY_DATABASE_URL`; no client-side cache in v1 (001-exercise-app)

- **Auth0** (SPA PKCE) + **PostgreSQL** + **Drizzle ORM** + **Drizzle Kit** + **HTTP API** (JWT validated); contract: `specs/app-base/contracts/openapi.yaml`
- **React 19**, **Vite**, TypeScript strict, **Node 20+**; optional client cache — server is source of truth (`specs/app-base`)
- Constitution **Principle III** exception documented in `specs/app-base/plan.md` **Complexity Tracking** (amend constitution before release)

## Project Structure

